[[Category:OntologySync-managed-resource]]

CNMF-E is a computational method designed specifically for one-photon (Miniscope) calcium imaging data. It separates the fluorescence signal of individual neurons from the large, fluctuating background that is characteristic of single-photon widefield imaging through a GRIN lens.

== Why It Matters ==
One-photon imaging produces more background contamination than two-photon imaging. Standard cell extraction methods (e.g., PCA/ICA) struggle with this. CNMF-E models the background explicitly, enabling reliable extraction of individual neuron traces from Miniscope recordings.
